Kubernetes DevOps Assignment Notes

- Created self-hosted Kubernetes cluster using kubeadm on AWS EC2 Ubuntu 22.04
- Configured Flannel CNI networking
- Installed Helm package manager
- Deployed Spark Operator using Helm
- Executed SparkPi sample job
- Installed PostgreSQL, MongoDB, and Redis
- Configured local-path storage provisioner for Persistent Volumes
- Performed PostgreSQL CRUD operations
- Performed Redis CRUD operations

Challenges Faced
- Limited AWS Free Tier resources caused some pods to remain in Pending state
- Fixed PersistentVolumeClaim issue using local-path provisioner
- Reduced memory usage for lightweight deployments

Outcome
- Successfully completed Kubernetes setup and service deployments with screenshots and documentation
